annotation.TEXT: And of course, don't drop down onto the first low row of blocks in this stretch!
Whoa, that's right. The level switches to a Bowser fire generator here. Also, I remember that I must stay on the top route here!
Oof! Well, that sucked... I tried to do the trick again with that guy and screwed it up.
Yeah, yeah. I've been fooling around for too long in this level. I'll be done quickly.
Not firing at me yet? I know these cannons do work... Oh, wait...
Now for 1-H (5-1), and I'm going to use tool-assistance to help me reach the pipe above the start.
Honestly, this hack would be so much better if it didn't have all these game-breaking flaws, because a lot of the level design is quite interesting.
Space-time rewind count: 19
Okay, I'm prepared to time-travel again if needed, but I want to see if attempting to get fireworks here will halt the game...
Yep. Too bad I can't destroy him this time.
Hi, Bowser! Bye, Bowser!
Ah, yes. This trick. If you remain overlapping a koopa/parakoopa from the point when you first stomp it, you won't get hurt.
Hello, and welcome back to New Strange Mario Bros.! Alright, let's resume with 1-F (4-3) here...
Will getting any fireworks halt the game here like back in 1-8?
Now for 1-I (5-2). I'll certainly take these two easy 1-ups, but I'm not gonna bother with the central power up block this time.
Okay, here's a good place to check that bullet cannon thing. Now, exactly how far away to I need to be for it to shoot at me?
Now for 1-M (6-2). I wonder how many of this level's pipes will reset the level...
Nice, I nailed that twice in a row.
(BTW, according to Garfield and Friends, "Gorsh" is Samoan for "Splut".)

Hey there, stupid glitch involving my keyboard controls not being at the highlighted-with-the-cursor-blinking-in-it text box that I just clicked on and instead still being on the video player and screwing with that and my mental state. BURN TO THE GROUND!
TAS-ing now.
Wow, three times in a row! I'm good at that, apparently!

2 Podoboos + 2 Toads + 1 Platform sprite... Yep, I was already at the sprite limit, which is why those cannons weren't firing at me at all there. Nuts. I'll try to find a better place to check that out later.
I wouldn't expect there to be any differences between 1-L and 6-1, unless the hacker put some "5-3 or later" sprites in this level, but I doubt that.
Still no life-ending collision with that block (and I actually tried to bump into it that time, just for the humor value).
Nope, looks like we're good this time!
Note: I don't have to worry about those first two cannons shooting me at all because they were on the first screen of the level, which prevents them from being able to fire for some reason.

Well, that one does. Now, I'm going to wait until near the end of the level before checking another pipe, so if I pass by any world 1 pointers along the way for any of the pipe exits, I'll end up wherever that pointer goes.
What, really? So, neither of these pipes in this dead end down here are enterable? Well, then surely there's a hidden block around here that'll let me escape, right?

The other platform there is just a regular dropping platform that has nothing to do with the balance lifts, so it still functions normally. Also, it's really nice of the game to give me two power ups right here!
I so expected to bump into that block and fall to my death that time.
Ah, okay. Once I'm that close, it won't fire. Looks like about 2¼ tiles away from the cannon or closer is the safe zone.
Unsurprisingly, that pipe reset the level.
Nuts. I wanted to double kill the Hammer Bro. and Goomba there.
Yep, though I wonder if it's possible that I'll hit my head on that block there. Well, if that happens later on, nuts to me, I guess.
That was pretty cool.
Yep, as long as the shell never completely leaves my hitbox, the game will never register it as hitting me again.
IDCLIP!
And, now that I've checked that pipe, I can now say, "Screw this. I'm outta here!"
And I added a little bit of rapid-fire A to the mix for a second there.
Well, at least I had just passed midpoint, and the way the game works, Bowser and his bridge didn't appear upon me respawning here, so that's good. But, why did I fall through that platform?
Since we've already seen this level enough times, I'll just race through it quickly.
Huh. I didn't know that hidden block was there. Okay, now this time, I'll just take the upper route so that I don't accidentally go down a pipe while dealing with Buzzy.
Oh, and yes, regardless of how far I got in world 1, once I hit an axe to clear the world, I'm sent to world 2-1.
Wow, so this is just more bad level design here, I guess.
Hey there, stationary spiny. BURN TO THE GROUND!
Huh. I wonder if the world number influences which behavior pattern the Bloopers use?
Now for 1-J (5-3). However, it will be completely identical to 1-3, because the game still thinks I'm in world 1, so platform sprites won't shrink, and "5-3 or later" enemies won't show up.
To be continued...
DOUBLE KILL!
Whoops, missed the Blooper somehow. Well, he's fleeing from me, so whatever. I'll let him live.
Demo count: 35
Gorsh!
I felt I was late as I made the jump there. If only I didn't stumble a bit near the top of the stairs...
MULTI KILL!
Ah, now over here, I'll check the pipes.
MULTI KILL!
Now, I could certainly wedge myself between the wall and left edge of the screen and jump onto the roof, but I don't want to do that quite yet...
Anyway, here's 1-L (6-1).
And, I'm back here again! I hope you all enjoyed that pointless sneak peek of 2-1! Now, this time, I won't hit the axe, but instead, I'll play with this koopa!

Ah, the very last pipe in the final staircase worked, but it just reset the level again. Maybe that would've taken me to the world 3/6 "sky bonus" area if I had entered it in world 6-2 the first time around.
MULTI KILL!
Because, you see, I want to check this pipe over here first.
Nope, I'm good this time. I wonder what caused that issue back in 1-8, then?
Oh, isn't this the level that's got multiple Bowsers?
Demo count: 34
Okay, got the six fireworks this time!
Now, I remember that a big jump from the highest hidden block here works really well.
You liar. This isn't 6-1. This is 1-L!
Oh, right. Broken midpoint. Gotta time-travel.
Demo count: 33
Fake Kaizo trap count: 9
DOUBLE KILL!
Yahhh!
Aw... Nuts. The pipe doesn't even go anywhere. So, that quick little TAS period there was for nothing meaningful. Oh, well. Now, let's return to non-TAS gameplay.
Umm... What? Did I just fall THROUGH that platform?!
Well, that'll be all for this episode. Next time, I'll be resuming with world 1-N (6-3). And maybe, if the levels go fast enough, I might finish everything up next time! But, we'll see...
I was gonna wait and check the pipes near the end of the level. Oh, well. Shouldn't take me too long to get back there.

Oh, yeah. Bullet cannons give you a lot more leeway in the first SMB than in any later Mario games (I think), and won't fire unless you're at least about 2.5 tiles away. Let's see exactly how far away I have to be before they start shooting at me...

Yeah, in case you can't tell, I'm getting more and more frustrated as I keep encountering that stupid glitch with the comment box and annotation editor text box, which has be plaguing me for... I don't know how many months/years now.
Now for 1-G (4-4), and I'm just gonna take the easy way out this time, since I most likely have to go this way to reach the flagpole anyway.
Alright, nailed it that time.
Now I can make the remaining Bowsers BURN! BURN TO THE GROUND! BURN! BURN TO THE GROUND! WOO! TRI-FORMATION!
I started pressing the rapid-fire B key here for no real reason.
Oh, I never knew that hidden block was there. Also, I'm glad that there are no flying cheepos here (like there are in 5-3)!

Uh, huh. Thought so. I know what the problem is. If only one platform in a pair of balance lifts spawns, it will be intangible for whatever reason, so the player can't interact with it at all. I think the sprite limit caused the right "balance lift" platform to not spawn the first time, and the left one's proximity to midpoint keeps it from spawning on subsequent times.
And, just like last level, 1-K will be completely identical to 1-8 and 2-4, without the differences 5-4 would have.
D'oh! I missed!
And, as expected, the pipe reset the level (instead of sending me to that horrible underwater "bonus" room).
Oh, right. The axe. Sure, I'll hit that one more time, and then go back in time afterwards.
D'oh! I didn't want to go down that pipe!

Nuts, just missed again!
